# Method

## Participants

`r n_participants` participants completed the experiment, comprising `r n_l1` L1 Spanish speakers (IDs beginning with 1) and `r n_l2` L2 Spanish learners (IDs beginning with 2).

## Procedure

Participants completed a three-phase Spanish stress-suffix association task in PsychoPy. The pre-test consisted of 360 trials across 6 blocks, followed by a 120-trial training phase with feedback, and concluded with a 360-trial post-test (parallel structure to the pre-test). On each trial, participants heard a spoken stimulus and selected between *PRESENTE* and *PASADO* response options. Stimuli varied factorially in verb stress (paroxytone, oxytone) and suffix tense (present, past), with match/mismatch conditions defined by the verb-suffix pairing.

## Analysis

Response time (RT) analyses were conducted on correct trials only, with exclusions for responses faster than 200 ms or slower than 5,000 ms. All analyses were run in R using the tidyverse. Group-level means were computed in two steps to avoid bias from unequal cell sizes: trial-level data were first averaged within participant, then averaged across participants.

# Results

## Overall Performance by Phase and Group

```{r overall-table}
library(knitr)

overall <- by_grp |>
  mutate(
    Accuracy = fmt_pct(accuracy),
    RT       = fmt_rt(rt),
    Phase    = stringr::str_to_title(as.character(phase))
  ) |>
  select(Group = group, Phase, Accuracy, `RT (correct)` = RT,
         `n` = n_participants)

kable(overall,
      caption = "Mean accuracy and reaction time by group and phase.",
      align = c("l", "l", "r", "r", "r"))
```

```{r overall-prose, results='asis'}
# Build APA-style paragraph from the data
make_phase_line <- function(grp_label, grp_code) {
  rows <- by_grp |> filter(group == grp_code) |> arrange(phase)
  pre  <- rows |> filter(phase == "pre")
  post <- rows |> filter(phase == "post")
  trn  <- rows |> filter(phase == "training")

  parts <- c()
  if (nrow(pre) > 0)
    parts <- c(parts, sprintf("pre-test (*M* = %s, RT = %s)",
                              fmt_pct(pre$accuracy), fmt_rt(pre$rt)))
  if (nrow(trn) > 0)
    parts <- c(parts, sprintf("training (*M* = %s, RT = %s)",
                              fmt_pct(trn$accuracy), fmt_rt(trn$rt)))
  if (nrow(post) > 0)
    parts <- c(parts, sprintf("post-test (*M* = %s, RT = %s)",
                              fmt_pct(post$accuracy), fmt_rt(post$rt)))

  sprintf("%s speakers showed accuracy at %s.",
          grp_label, paste(parts, collapse = ", "))
}

cat(make_phase_line("L1 Spanish", "L1"), "\n\n")
if (n_l2 > 0) cat(make_phase_line("L2 Spanish", "L2"), "\n\n")

# Pre-to-post change
change_tbl <- by_grp |>
  filter(phase %in% c("pre", "post")) |>
  select(group, phase, accuracy, rt) |>
  pivot_wider(names_from = phase, values_from = c(accuracy, rt)) |>
  mutate(
    acc_change = accuracy_post - accuracy_pre,
    rt_change  = rt_post - rt_pre
  )

for (g in change_tbl$group) {
  row <- change_tbl |> filter(group == g)
  cat(sprintf(
    "From pre- to post-test, %s speakers showed an accuracy change of %+.1f percentage points and an RT change of %+d ms.\n\n",
    g, 100 * row$acc_change, round(1000 * row$rt_change)
  ))
}
```

